{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778109267,"nonce":"Jg5bXqfffaD2Dddz2z9Ru/PqIgQ=","title":"Riccati flavor-(b) extension: support ΔA·x model-class structural disturbance","message":"Follow-up to the C\u0026S Eq. 15 Q,R reproduction test (`19b9921`, merged via `cd229998`) which xfailed with Δv ≤ 0 on the C\u0026S plant even with the paper's faithful Q,R. Diagnosis (per `c99ad9d` comment): the production Riccati's `B_w` is most likely flavor-(a) additive-force, while C\u0026S 2019 used flavor-(b) `ΔA·x·dt + C·dw` model-class disturbance. No Q,R schedule will close the gap — the disturbance channel formulation itself needs to change.\n\n## Scope\n\nExtend `src/rlrmp/analysis/hinf_riccati.py` to support a flavor-(b) disturbance channel where the adversary perturbs entries of the augmented `A` matrix (e.g., velocity-row block, or a structured low-rank `ΔA`), constrained in a Frobenius / spectral ball.\n\n## API sketch\n\nTwo options (implementer's choice):\n1. New function `solve_hinf_riccati_modelclass(plant, schedule, gamma, *, delta_A_structure, delta_A_budget)`.\n2. Extend the existing `solve_hinf_riccati` with an optional `delta_A_constraint` parameter and dispatch internally.\n\n`RiccatiSolution` value type may need a flag indicating which flavor was solved.\n\n## Tests\n\n- C\u0026S plant + faithful Eq. 15 Q,R + flavor-(b) ΔA disturbance reproduces the paper's qualitative claim (Δv \u003e 0). This converts the existing xfailed `test_cs_faithful_qr_velocity_inflation` into a passing test under the new flavor (or keeps both flavors with separate tests).\n- LQR limit (γ → ∞) recovers nominal LQR K regardless of disturbance class.\n- Numerical conditioning bounded across γ ∈ [1.05γ\\*, 5γ\\*] (same as the existing flavor-(a) test).\n\n## Cross-refs\n\n- `c723082` — `LinearDynamicsAdversary` (training-side flavor-(b) lift; same conceptual class for the training adversary). The Riccati extension here is the analytic teacher analog.\n- `19b9921` — the C\u0026S Q,R test that surfaced this finding (merged xfailed).\n- `5a44bd3` — original Riccati implementation (closed; this issue extends it).\n- `c99ad9d` — training-methods coord (where this concern's discussion lives).\n- `db35426` — H∞ Riccati teacher distillation (depends on this for the flavor-(b) teacher).\n\n## Why this matters\n\nThe natural Riccati-side analog of `c723082`. Having the analytic Riccati K for a flavor-(b) disturbance is essential as: (a) the **teacher policy** for distillation (`db35426`), (b) the **baseline** against which `c723082`-trained ΔA-adversary controllers are compared, (c) closing the C\u0026S replication gap (the empirical anchor for synthesis_review's `(a) ⊊ (b)` claim).\n\nLabel: `feature`.","files":null}]}